    {
      "id": "1914750c-f3ba-8058-aa45-ebdfdde4a8cf",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There don’t seem be many studies actually looking into identifying the optimal time to identify dropout. Authors use demographics and academic data from 935 students from an engineering school and use DT predict dropout (withdrawal). To identify the optimal time, authors choose 3 distinct moments of prediction during the first-year’s first semester. Authors find academic is a good early predictor of dropout. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
